[{"data":1,"prerenderedAt":2149},["ShallowReactive",2],{"header-locale:\u002Fen\u002Fnodejs\u002F2023\u002F10\u002F08\u002Fday-24-deploying-to-zeabur\u002F":3,"page:\u002Fen\u002Fnodejs\u002F2023\u002F10\u002F08\u002Fday-24-deploying-to-zeabur\u002F":4,"alt:\u002Fen\u002Fnodejs\u002F2023\u002F10\u002F08\u002Fday-24-deploying-to-zeabur\u002F":3,"prev-next:\u002Fen\u002Fnodejs\u002F2023\u002F10\u002F08\u002Fday-24-deploying-to-zeabur\u002F":2124,"related:\u002Fen\u002Fnodejs\u002F2023\u002F10\u002F08\u002Fday-24-deploying-to-zeabur\u002F":2133},"\u002Fnodejs\u002F20231008\u002F2016996949\u002F",{"id":5,"title":6,"abbrlink":7,"altUrl":3,"body":8,"category":2108,"date":2109,"description":26,"extension":2110,"lang":2111,"meta":2112,"navigation":275,"path":2113,"readingMinutes":2114,"seo":2115,"standalone":2116,"stem":2117,"tags":2118,"tldr":2121,"updated":2109,"url":2122,"__hash__":2123},"content\u002Fen\u002FNodejs\u002Fday-24-deploying-to-zeabur.md","Day 24 - Deploying to Zeabur","8429141456",{"type":9,"value":10,"toc":2100},"minimark",[11,19,24,27,30,33,36,39,55,58,61,70,73,77,80,83,168,192,195,237,240,701,704,989,992,1386,1389,1666,1669,1753,1756,1771,1784,1787,1793,1796,1802,1805,1811,1814,1820,1823,1829,1832,1838,1841,1844,1850,1853,1859,1862,1868,1871,1877,1882,1885,1891,1897,1903,1906,1911,1918,1923,1930,2022,2026,2029,2047,2050,2059,2062,2065,2068,2077,2080,2083,2090,2093,2096],[12,13,14],"p",{},[15,16],"img",{"alt":17,"src":18},"Zeabur","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002Fblog\u002Fnodejs\u002Fithelp-nodejs-2023\u002F%E6%88%AA%E5%9C%96%202023-09-08%2014.22.48.png",[20,21,23],"h2",{"id":22},"intro","Intro",[12,25,26],{},"After getting the basic concept of servers in the previous post, of course we have to actually deploy a project to a server.",[20,28,17],{"id":29},"zeabur",[12,31,32],{},"Zeabur is a PaaS platform. What's PaaS? Platform as a Service.",[12,34,35],{},"A bit vague? Let me give an example. Say you want to build a house. What do you need? Foundation, cement, bricks, wood, etc. — not to mention designing the house itself. These are all things you need to do.",[12,37,38],{},"The PaaS concept is like hiring a professional construction company to build it for you. The company provides services like design, construction, materials, etc. — you just tell them what house you want and they build it. That's the PaaS concept.",[12,40,41,42,46,47,50,51,54],{},"So in this concept, you're the ",[43,44,45],"strong",{},"developer",", the construction company is the ",[43,48,49],{},"PaaS platform",", and the house is the ",[43,52,53],{},"project",". You just focus on project development without worrying about server issues — that's the benefit of PaaS.",[12,56,57],{},"There are many common PaaS platforms — for example, Heroku (which became paid earlier) is a PaaS platform. So we don't have to worry too much about server issues — just register an account, create a project, deploy the project. Pretty convenient.",[12,59,60],{},"The core idea of PaaS platforms is abstracting away the complex server management work, so you can focus on project development. Really convenient for beginners.",[62,63,64],"blockquote",{},[12,65,66,69],{},[43,67,68],{},"Note","\nThere's also IaaS (Infrastructure as a Service) and SaaS (Software as a Service), but those aren't what we're covering here. Look them up if interested.",[12,71,72],{},"Why am I picking Zeabur? Because Zeabur is a Taiwanese PaaS platform — gotta support local platforms. Plus Zeabur offers a free plan ($5\u002Fmonth), and it's really convenient. So let's use Zeabur to deploy our project.",[20,74,76],{"id":75},"deploying","Deploying",[12,78,79],{},"I'll walk you through deploying the previous post's project to Zeabur step by step. You can also try first and come back if you have issues.",[12,81,82],{},"Below are the corresponding commands and the code we expect to deploy — making sure your code matches mine for smooth deployment:",[84,85,90],"pre",{"className":86,"code